  "body": "**Description**\r\n\r\nThe Solidity compiler accepts numeric literals of arbitrary precision. But computing those literals can take arbitrary high time.\r\nWhen the following sample contract is compiled, the compiler runs for several hours (weâ€™ve not waited until it finishes):\r\n\r\ncontract BIGNUMTEST {\r\nfunction bignum() {\r\nuint c;\r\nc=1E10000000;\r\n}\r\n}\r\n\r\n**Recommendations**\r\n\r\nLimit the size of numeric literals.\r\n",
